cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.SE 

This paper discusses XML query languages, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper compares query languages in the tradition of database query languages. The paper also discusses languages for extracting and restructuring XML content, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the ongoing discussion and development of a standard for XML query language.
